content.problemStatement:
You're building a program to categorize a person's age into different life stages. Use `if-else if` conditions to classify the person as a `Child`, `Teenager`, or `Adult` based on their age.

Consider the following C code:

```cpp
#include

int main() {
    int age = 16;

    if (age ___ 12) {
        printf("Child\n");
    } ___ (age ___ 19) {
        printf("Teenager\n");
    } else {
        printf("Adult\n");
    }

    return 0;
}
```

